How to create the pg_statsinfo rpm.
=====================================

1. Create required folders
$ mkdir -p ~/rpmbuild/{BUILD,RPMS,SOURCES,SPECS,SRPMS}

2. Create .rpmmacros file
$ echo "%_topdir %(echo $HOME)/rpmbuild" > ~/.rpmmacros

3. Copy the pg_statsinfo tarball and SPEC file
$ cp pg_statsinfo-X.X.X.tar.gz ~/rpmbuild/SOURCES
$ cp pg_statsinfo.spec ~/rpmbuild/SPECS

4. Edit the SPEC file
edit the following parameters to be match with PostgreSQL version.

$ vi ~/rpmbuild/SPECS/pg_statsinfo.spec
----------------------------------------
* %define _pgdir   /usr/pgsql-9.4
* BuildRequires:   postgresql94-devel
----------------------------------------

5. Building the RPM package
$ rpmbuild -ba ~/rpmbuild/SPECS/pg_statsinfo.spec


Requirements
-------------------------------------
The following packages should be installed.

* rpm-build
* postgresql-devel
